#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><h2>
#: sedout/security.html:257
msgid "<span>1.2. </span>Untrusted SQLite Database Files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p>
#: sedout/security.html:259
msgid ""
"Applications that read or write SQLite database files of uncertain "
"provenance should take precautions enumerated below."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p>
#: sedout/security.html:262
msgid ""
"Even if the application does not deliberately accept database files from "
"untrusted sources, beware of attacks in which a local database file is "
"altered.  For best security, any database file which might have ever been "
"writable by an agent in a different security domain should be treated as "
"suspect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><ol><li>
#: sedout/security.html:270
msgid ""
"If the application includes any <a href=\"appfunc.html\">custom SQL "
"functions</a> or <a href=\"vtab.html#customvtab\">custom virtual tables</a> "
"that have side effects or that might leak privileged information, then the "
"application should use one or more of the techniques below to prevent a "
"maliciously crafted database schema from surreptitiously running those SQL "
"functions and/or virtual tables for nefarious purposes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><ol><li><ol><li>
#: sedout/security.html:277
msgid ""
"Invoke <a href=\"c3ref/db_config.html\">sqlite3_db_config</a>(db,<a "
"href=\"c3ref/c_dbconfig_defensive.html#sqlitedbconfigtrustedschema\">SQLITE_DBCONFIG_TRUSTED_SCHEMA</a>,0,0)  "
"on each <a href=\"c3ref/sqlite3.html\">database connection</a> as soon as it "
"is opened."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><ol><li><ol><li>
#: sedout/security.html:279
msgid ""
"Run the <a href=\"pragma.html#pragma_trusted_schema\">PRAGMA "
"trusted_schema=OFF</a> statement on each database connection as soon as it "
"is opened."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><ol><li><ol><li>
#: sedout/security.html:281
msgid ""
"Compile SQLite using the <a "
"href=\"compile.html#trusted_schema\">-DSQLITE_TRUSTED_SCHEMA=0</a> "
"compile-time option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><ol><li><ol><li>
#: sedout/security.html:282
msgid ""
"Disable the surreptitious use of custom SQL functions and virtual tables by "
"setting the <a "
"href=\"c3ref/c_deterministic.html#sqlitedirectonly\">SQLITE_DIRECTONLY</a> "
"flag on all custom SQL functions and the <a "
"href=\"c3ref/c_vtab_constraint_support.html#sqlitevtabdirectonly\">SQLITE_VTAB_DIRECTONLY</a> "
"flag on all custom virtual tables."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><ol><li><p>
#: sedout/security.html:288
msgid ""
"If the application does not use triggers or views, consider disabling the "
"unused capabilities with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><ol><li><blockquote><pre>
#: sedout/security.html:291
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<a href=\"c3ref/db_config.html\">sqlite3_db_config</a>(db,<a "
"href=\"c3ref/c_dbconfig_defensive.html#sqlitedbconfigenabletrigger\">SQLITE_DBCONFIG_ENABLE_TRIGGER</a>,0,0);\n"
"<a href=\"c3ref/db_config.html\">sqlite3_db_config</a>(db,<a "
"href=\"c3ref/c_dbconfig_defensive.html#sqlitedbconfigenableview\">SQLITE_DBCONFIG_ENABLE_VIEW</a>,0,0);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><p>
#: sedout/security.html:298
msgid ""
"For reading database files that are unusually high-risk, such as database "
"files that are received from remote machines, and possibly from anonymous "
"contributors, the following extra precautions might be justified.  These "
"added defenses come with performance costs, however, and so may not be "
"appropriate in every situation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><p><ol><li>
#: sedout/security.html:306
msgid ""
"Run <a href=\"pragma.html#pragma_integrity_check\">PRAGMA "
"integrity_check</a> or <a href=\"pragma.html#pragma_quick_check\">PRAGMA "
"quick_check</a> on the database as the first SQL statement after opening the "
"database files and prior to running any other SQL statements.  Reject and "
"refuse to process any database file containing errors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><p><ol><li>
#: sedout/security.html:312
msgid ""
"Enable the <a href=\"pragma.html#pragma_cell_size_check\">PRAGMA "
"cell_size_check=ON</a> setting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><p><ol><li>
#: sedout/security.html:316
msgid ""
"Do not enable memory-mapped I/O.  In other words, make sure that <a "
"href=\"pragma.html#pragma_mmap_size\">PRAGMA mmap_size=0</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><p><h1>
#: sedout/security.html:321
msgid "<span>2. </span>Summary"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p><p><p><p>
#: sedout/security.html:324
msgid ""
"The precautions above are not required in order to use SQLite safely with "
"potentially hostile inputs.  However, they do provide an extra layer of "
"defense against zero-day exploits and are encouraged for applications that "
"pass data from untrusted sources into SQLite."
msgstr ""

